An overview of the article selection process followed the PRISMA guidelines  [46]  and was described in Fig.  1 . An overall of 666 articles were retrieved through the searches within the three databases. After screening the title, abstract and full-text, 575 articles were filtered out by our exclusion criteria. On top of that, 8 articles which are proposals or extended abstracts describing a system development in progress, were excluded because no related follow-up studies were found at the end of the database screening. 17 additional works were included, due to the aforementioned extra manual search based on the references of highly relevant articles. Articles describing the same shared PI system were combined and counted as one case in our list. Finally, 100 items met all the inclusion criteria and were included in this literature review. The data were extracted using inductive thematic analysis  [35]  to formulate the predefined categories of features among the selected articles, as listed in Fig.  2 . After the first exclusion process, a cross review was performed by the second coder (name). Then the two coders settled the disagreements, summarized the characteristics, and refined the subcategories through a series of collaborative sessions.
